amdgpu: ps4 UVD GART bindings need PTE_WRITEABLE (v76d-β-2-A3)

A2 confirmed the firmware is alive and executing — it copied its real
1920 KB into a GTT BO bound at 0x300000000 and the VCPU's bring-up
preamble ran. Then a NEW fault appeared:

  VM_CONTEXT1_PROTECTION_FAULT_ADDR   0x00300000
  VM_CONTEXT1_PROTECTION_FAULT_STATUS 0x090BB010
  VM fault (0x10, vmid 4, pasid 0) at page 3145728, WRITE from 'UMC' (187)

Different from every previous fault:
  - PROTECTIONS=0x10 = bit 4 set, NOT bit 1 (PT walk) or bit 2/3
    (PDE/PTE invalid). bit 4 = WRITE_PROTECTION_FAULT — write access
    rejected on a read-only page.
  - "write from 'UMC'" — firmware is now WRITING, not reading. The
    firmware advanced past read-only init and is trying to update
    its own state.
  - 187 retries — firmware retries the write many times before giving up.

This means the firmware is fully alive and trying to do real work.
The fix is one line: our PTEs need AMDGPU_PTE_WRITEABLE in addition
to AMDGPU_PTE_READABLE.

This patch adds WRITEABLE to all three of our GART bindings:
  - uvd_v4_2.c: the fw mirror at 0x300000000 (1920 KB) — primary write target
  - gmc_v7_0.c: dummy at 0x300000000 (fallback before fw mirror takes over)
  - gmc_v7_0.c: dummy at VA 0 (in case firmware also writes through
    a null pointer dereference)

Expected hardware signals:

  ✅ VCPU sets STATUS bit 1 within 2 seconds — firmware boots,
     ring test passes, UVD works!

  🟡 Fault moves to a different VA inside region 1 (firmware writes
     somewhere outside 0x300000000) — chase it.

  🟡 Fault moves to 0x3001E0000 or 0x300304000 — firmware advanced
     past region 1, needs region 2/3 bound (extend mirror).

  ❌ Same "write protection fault" at 0x300000 — WRITEABLE flag isn't
     enough; might need EXECUTABLE or some other PTE flag (look at
     full PTE permission set Sony uses in gbase_map flags 0x161).

Sony's gbase_map call from `gbase_create_vmid` for the per-vmid kernel
work area uses flags 0x161 = bits 0, 5, 6, 8. That maps to:
  bit 0 = VALID
  bit 5 = READABLE
  bit 6 = WRITEABLE
  bit 8 = something else (maybe SNOOPED or cache hint)

So Sony's flags include WRITEABLE. We do too with this patch. Bit 8
might be a future iteration if we still see issues.

Signed-off-by: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gmc_v7_0.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gmc_v7_0.c
@@ -788,7 +788,7 @@

 		amdgpu_gart_bind(adev, 0x300000000ULL, 1, &fw_dummy,
 				 AMDGPU_PTE_VALID | AMDGPU_PTE_SYSTEM |
-				 AMDGPU_PTE_READABLE);
+				 AMDGPU_PTE_READABLE | AMDGPU_PTE_WRITEABLE);
 		DRM_INFO("ps4: bound dummy page at GART virtual 0x300000000 "
 			 "(pa=0x%llx) for UVD fw access\n",
 			 (unsigned long long)fw_dummy);
@@ -809,7 +809,7 @@
 		 */
 		amdgpu_gart_bind(adev, 0x0ULL, 1, &fw_dummy,
 				 AMDGPU_PTE_VALID | AMDGPU_PTE_SYSTEM |
-				 AMDGPU_PTE_READABLE);
+				 AMDGPU_PTE_READABLE | AMDGPU_PTE_WRITEABLE);
 		DRM_INFO("ps4: bound dummy page at GART virtual 0x0 "
 			 "(pa=0x%llx) for UVD fw null-deref\n",
 			 (unsigned long long)fw_dummy);
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/uvd_v4_2.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/uvd_v4_2.c
@@ -523,7 +523,7 @@
 	amdgpu_gart_bind(adev, PS4_UVD_FW_MIRROR_VA, num_pages,
 			 uvd_fw_mirror_bo->tbo.ttm->dma_address,
 			 AMDGPU_PTE_VALID | AMDGPU_PTE_SYSTEM |
-			 AMDGPU_PTE_READABLE);
+			 AMDGPU_PTE_READABLE | AMDGPU_PTE_WRITEABLE);
 	amdgpu_gart_invalidate_tlb(adev);

 	DRM_INFO("ps4 uvd: bound fw mirror at GART virtual 0x%llx "
